# SQLAlchemy Models

- All models inherit from `BaseModel` (`app.models.base`), which provides `id` (UUID), `created_at`, `updated_at`
- Use `Mapped[T]` with `mapped_column()` for all fields
- Register every new model in `app/models/__init__.py` so Alembic picks it up

```python
from app.models.base import BaseModel
from sqlalchemy import String, Boolean
from sqlalchemy.orm import Mapped, mapped_column

class User(BaseModel):
    __tablename__ = "users"

    email: Mapped[str] = mapped_column(String(255), unique=True, index=True, nullable=False)
```
